text: Normal seafood fried rice  charging customer $12 a packet, mind you don't have big prawn or big sotong

One of the better Zi char places that sell JB/Malaysian/Cantonese style food. This salted egg JB style pan fried bee hoon set me back 7 dollars without being too jelak and I am still able to taste the salted egg flavor. I wish the bee hoon could be more flavorful but nevertheless I think it is a creative and not bad eat Zi char dish.

Ordered 2 soups - Seaweed Tofu and Salted Vegetable Soup. 2 rice and 1 take away Vege Hoon .

Waited from 9pm  now 10pm.

Food served. AFTER we chasing the staff for about 5 times !

Reason in the end : one staff said - too many orders. 5 chefs inside . Later , another staff said machine spoilt . Orders not churned out.
Foods are excellent, service staff are quite bad and always mess up your order and have zero remorse over their mistakes.
